[The most effective EEE prevention is vaccination. The vaccine is usually combined with vaccines for West Nile virus and western equine encephalitis. Most owners usually vaccinate in the spring, but immunity to EEE is the shortest and wanes within about 3-4 months. Owners are encouraged to vaccinate every 3 to 4 months to protect against EEE.

In the United States, equine vaccines are available for eastern equine encephalomyelitis (or eastern equine encephalitis, EEE), western equine encephalomyelitis (WEE), Venezuelan equine encephalomyelitis (VEE), and West Nile virus encephalomyelitis.

For more information on Eastern equine encephalitis readers are encouraged to see the moderator's comment on ProMED-mail posting 20160726.4369305. - Mod.TG

